description:
Syncfusion’s pivot client for UWP is a .NET library that allows you to browse multidimensional data organized through an OLAP cube or relational data source. You can visualize the results in both graphical and tabular formats. The component can also be used to create and edit reports on-the-fly that are stored for later use.

	Key features:
	• Chart: Graphical representation of the data represented by symbols such as bars in a bar chart, lines in a line chart, or slices in a pie chart.
	• Grid: Tabular representation of data arranged in the form of rows and columns and categorized accordingly.
	• Slice and dice: Slice and dice the fields in OLAP and relational databases.
	• Pivot Browser: Add, rearrange, or remove fields to show the data in the component exactly as desired.
	• Toolbar: Toggle the pivot axis, export and manipulate the pivot report. Provides a rich UI experience.
	• Export: Export the pivot grid and pivot chart to PDF, Excel, Word, CSV, and other supported image formats.
	• Save and load: Saves the current session of the report in a XML file or as a stream for future use and reloads it whenever needed.

	Learn more: https://www.syncfusion.com/uwp-ui-controls/pivot-client?utm_source=nuget&utm_medium=listing
		  
	Documentation: https://help.syncfusion.com/uwp/pivot-client/overview?utm_source=nuget&utm_medium=listing
